# gated access list - WHITELIST by ASN (Autonomous System Number).
#
# One ASN per line, as "AS15169" or "15169". Blank lines and text
# after '#' are ignored. Requires geoip.enabled with an ASN database
# (geoip.asn_db) so gated can resolve each client's network.
#
# Whitelisting an ASN lets ALL of that network's addresses bypass the
# WAF — use it e.g. for a trusted crawler or your own hosting provider.
#
# Examples (commented out):
# AS15169   # Google (incl. Googlebot)
# AS8075    # Microsoft (incl. Bingbot)
